        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 2 at 2:22PM EDT by NWS Peachtree City GA</headline>
        <description>At 222 PM EDT, a strong thunderstorm was over Talona, or near
Ellijay, moving northeast at 25 mph.

HAZARD...40 to 50 mph wind, nickel sized hail and frequent cloud to
ground lightning.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Expect minor damage to tree limbs and blowing around of
light, unsecured objects.

Locations impacted include...
Ellijay, East Ellijay, Talona, Cartecay, Pisgah, Cherry Log, Roy, and
Roundtop.
</description>
        <instruction>People outdoors should seek shelter immediately. If you can hear
thunder, you are close enough to be struck by lightning.</instruction>
